    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>In historical western fashion, particularly in the 18th and 19th centuries, attire worn during the period of full mourning; generally refers to dress which is not only black but also of drab and lusterless materials. The term may also be applied to mourning costume of other cultures and time periods.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000001681/Livandi, Thesaurus of Clothing and Textile Terms, Personal Artifacts (1990)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Atuendo usado durante el periodo de luto total, generalmente se refiere al traje que es no es sólo negro si no que también de materiales sin gracia y opacos.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Rouwdrachten die de hoogste graad van rouwbetoon tot uitdrukking brengen; verwijst in het algemeen naar kledij die niet alleen zwart is, maar ook van sobere, niet-glanzende stof.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
